This paper is about neural image style transfer, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel model for multi-style transfer that involves learning an interpretable style representation, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves mathematical decomposition of styles into a common basis, which may suggest that it could be relevant to geometric reasoning (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves experiments with image data, which suggests that it could also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
